Poor English reading skills are to blame for bad grades in national examinations, Story Moja publishing house managing director Muthoni Garland has said.She said the mastery of the English language is the foundation for good grades.&ldquo;It makes learners understand what is asked and is the language used to answer the examination questions,&rdquo; Garland said.She spoke at Ithiani Primary School in Kitui Central subcounty on Thursday when she opened the library. Governor Julius Malombe&rsquo;s wife Edith Mawia was present. The school is one of the 29 beneficiaries of the county&rsquo;s library building project. Story Moja donated 1,000 books.Garland urged parents to start instilling a reading culture in children at the age of eight. She said parents should buy their children English story books.